column5: Looking to purchase some good looking custom ice rods (28" medum and 28"-30"medium heavy).  Mr. Spiel, do you still make yours?  Cheers,  S28
....I do. But I don't currently have any blanks for ice rods and I'm up to my eyeballs in musky rods right now. I'd be willing to bet your not wanting them for next winter!

Well I dont know anyone who is making custom ice rods but if you find out let me know. I was actually trying to find some the other day but nothing in Ontario. I'm looking for a medium heavy, 34"-38". Something nice and long for laker's and those quinte walleye.
Hi Spiel, I'm defiantly want them for this coming season. Thanks though.  FP: Will let you know if I find some.
Thorne Bros makes sweet customs, its in the US but they have super fast shipping. deadly laker rod
I've made a couple here and there too. I'm not exactly in Ontario any more though.
I can get them,I'm in the Oshawa area,pm me.
